Package: open-bastion
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Provides: libpam-openbastion
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 curl,
 jq,
 locales,
 debconf | debconf-2.0,
Recommends: auditd
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends},
Description: Open Bastion PAM/NSS module for SSH bastion authentication
 This PAM module enables Linux servers to authenticate users via
 Open Bastion, supporting both token-based authentication and
 key-based authorization with server groups support.

Package: open-bastion-builder
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 bash (>= 4.0),
 curl,
 openssl,
 jq,
 coreutils,
 openssh-client,
Recommends: yq
Description: Open Bastion deployment artefact builder
 Interactive tool for administrators to generate self-extracting
 shell installers and Ansible roles that deploy and configure
 Open Bastion (PAM/NSS + LLNG SSO) on target servers.
 .
 The builder is installed on the admin's workstation; the generated
 artefacts are then distributed to the production servers.

Package: open-bastion-desktop
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 open-bastion (>= ${source:Version}),
 lightdm,
 lightdm-webkit2-greeter,
Recommends: fonts-noto
Description: Open Bastion LightDM greeter for Desktop SSO
 A LightDM webkit2 greeter theme that enables desktop workstations to
 authenticate users via LemonLDAP::NG Single Sign-On.
 .
 Features:
  - SSO authentication via embedded LLNG portal iframe
  - Offline mode with cached credentials when server is unreachable
  - Multi-factor authentication support (TOTP, WebAuthn, etc.)
  - Session selection for multiple desktop environments
  - Modern, responsive design
